Two people were killed and two others injured on Monday by elephants in Meru and Tharaka-Nithi counties. The four elephants strayed from Meru National Park on Sunday night, officials said. In Tharaka a 17-year-old boy in Igumo village was killed while in Meru County a man from Nthambiro village was killed. A woman from Tharaka who was injured by the furious elephants is receiving treatment at Tharaka Sub-County Hospital. Meru National Park Senior Warden Tuqa Jirmo told the Nation by phone that Kenya Wild Life Service (KWS) rangers shot dead one of the elephants.  